# Ask Aunt Lurlene (zero-dependency Python)

An anonymous Southern advice column built like a modern vintage newspaper.
Readers submit anonymously; Aunt Lurlene logs in, gets breaking-news popups,
and publishes answers that **everyone** then sees.

## Why this version deploys cleanly

It uses **only Python's standard library** — no Flask, no gunicorn, no
psycopg2, **no packages at all**. The build step that kept failing was
`pip install`. There is now nothing for pip to install, so that step cannot
fail. The whole web page is also embedded inside `app.py`, so there is no
separate HTML file for the host to mis-serve either.

## Files (only one matters)
| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `app.py` | The entire app: web server, database, and the embedded page |
| `requirements.txt` | Intentionally comment-only — tells pip there's nothing to install |

Admin login (change for production): username `angie` / password `password123`

