## Deploy to Railway

1. Get the files into GitHub. Easiest and most reliable: GitHub Desktop —
   install it, create/clone your repo, drop `app.py` and `requirements.txt` in,
   commit, push. Make sure they sit at the TOP LEVEL of the repo, not in a
   subfolder.
2. railway.app -> New Project -> Deploy from GitHub repo -> pick your repo.
   Railway detects Python and runs `python app.py`.
3. Settings -> Networking -> Generate Domain -> visit the URL. Done.

No database setup is required for it to run.

### If a previous deploy is cached/failing
Make sure `requirements.txt` no longer contains any `gunicorn`/`web:` line.
Replace its entire contents with the comment-only version in this package
(or just delete the file — this app needs no packages).

