## Run locally
    python app.py
    # open http://localhost:3000
No installs needed.

## How the two key features work
- Answers update for everyone: published answers are written to the database
  and served from it; the front page re-fetches every 30 seconds, so every
  visitor on the live site stays in sync.
- Only Lurlene gets popups: popups come from /api/admin/new-since, which
  requires the admin login. Only her logged-in browser polls it.

## About storage (important)
By default the app stores data in a local SQLite file. On the running site,
all visitors share that data, so Lurlene's answers appear for everyone
immediately. Two caveats with default file storage on Railway:
- A redeploy resets the data (the filesystem is rebuilt).
- It assumes a single instance (Railway's default).

To make data permanent and survive redeploys, switch to PostgreSQL:
1. In Railway: New -> Database -> Add PostgreSQL (this sets DATABASE_URL).
2. In requirements.txt, uncomment the psycopg2-binary==2.9.9 line.
3. Redeploy. The app detects DATABASE_URL and uses Postgres automatically.

## For real-world use
Change ADMIN_PASS, and set ADMIN_USER/ADMIN_PASS as Railway variables rather
than leaving the defaults.
